decision_conditions:
Condition : 1 - This development shall be begun within 3 years from 18 October 2012.
To comply with Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990.

Condition : 2 - For each phase of the development details of those parts of the site not covered by buildings, including any parking areas, access ways, surface treatment and boundary treatment, shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority before any works (excluding demolition) are commenced within that phase.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2434.
To ensure a high quality of development in compliance with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 3 - For each phase of the development details of proposed boundary treatment shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority. Such details as may be approved shall be carried out prior to occupation of each relevant phase of the development.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2434.
To ensure a satisfactory appearance and to accord with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 4 - Notwithstanding any materials specified in the application, details and samples of materials proposed to be used on all external surfaces for each phase of the development shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority before any works (excluding demolition) are commenced within that phase, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved materials.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by references 2014/2965, 2014/3527, 2014/6005, and 2015/5139.
In order to assess the suitability of the proposed materials, in the interests of the appearance of the locality, in accordance with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 5 - Details of arrangements for the storage of refuse shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority before each phase of the development begins (excluding demolition), unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority. The works shall be carried out before the permitted use starts in each phase.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2090.
In the interests of amenity and hygiene, in accordance with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 6 - For each phase of the development, details of surrounding noise environment and insulation against external noise generated by roads and railway and anticipated noise generated by the commercial units and community centre (to good/reasonable standard of Table 5 of the British Standard BS8233 as identified within the "Sustainable Design and Construction SPG (2006)) shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority. The approved measures shall be installed prior to the commencement of the occupation of the building. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2016/0197.
To protect the occupiers of the building(s), in accordance with Council policies DMH4(ii)

Condition : 7 - Details of noise insulation measures to provide effective resistance to the transmission of airborne and impact sound between the commercial and community uses and the residential units shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority. The approved measures shall be completed prior to the commencement of the use of the relevant premises. 
To safeguard the amenities of adjoining occupiers, in accordance with Council policy DMS1.

Condition : 8 - For each phase of the development details of facilities for people with disabilities shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority before development (excluding demolition) commences. Such facilities as approved shall be provided prior to the occupation of each phase and maintained thereafter. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2090.
To ensure that disabled people can satisfactorily use the building(s), in accordance with Council policy DMS(i)

Condition : 9 - The facilities for people with disabilities shown on the approved plans shall be provided prior to the occupation of the buildings/commencement of the uses, and maintained thereafter.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2090. 
To ensure that disabled people can satisfactorily use the building(s), in accordance with Council policy DMS(i)

Condition : 10 - Details of any external ventilation equipment, including ducting, shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority before installation. The ventilation equipment shall be implemented in accordance with the approved details.  
In the interests of local amenity and visual appearance, and in accordance with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 11 - Details of landscaping, play space/equipment and treatment of parts of the site not covered by buildings, to include species of new planting and any existing plants/trees to be retained, shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority before the commencement of each phase of the development (excluding demolition). All planting, seeding or turfing, landscape works, playspace/equipment included in the approved details shall be carried out prior to the occupation of any part of the relevant phase, or in accordance with a programme agreed in writing with the local planning authority.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2434.
To ensure a satisfactory appearance, in accordance with Council policy DMS1.

Condition : 12 - Details of the means of protecting the trees (which are to be retained) from damage during building works, including site supervision arrangements, shall be submitted to and approved by the local planning authority before the start of any demolition, building or other work for each phase of the development. Such protection shall be installed and retained as approved throughout the period of works.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2012/5199. Phase 2 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2016/4298.
To safeguard the trees in the interest of the amenity of the area, in accordance with Council policy DMO5 (b)

Condition : 13 - Prior to planting in each phase of the development, details of trees, including size, species and location are to be approved in writing by the local planning authority.  The planting shall be carried out in accordance with those details.  Any trees which within a period of five years from the completion of the development is found to be dead, removed or becomes seriously damaged or diseased, shall be replaced in the next planting season with others of a similar size and species. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2434.
To safeguard the trees in the interest of the amenity of the area, in accordance with Council policy DMO5 (a)

Condition : 14 - The screening/enclosure to the balconies/roof terraces, shown on the approved drawings, shall be completed before any use of the balconies/terraces commence, and retained permanently afterwards.  
To protect the privacy of neighbours and prevent overlooking in accordance with Council policy DMS1(c)

Condition : 16 - The parking areas shown on the approved plans shall be provided before the occupation of the associated phase of the development, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority, and shall be retained for parking purposes for the users of the development and for no other purpose. 
To ensure adequate arrangements are made for off-street parking in accordance with Council policy DMT2.

Condition : 17 - Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015, or any future enactment of that Order, no windows, doors or glazed areas (other than such as may be shown on the approved plans) shall be formed in any wall of the buildings without the prior written consent of the local planning authority.
To protect the privacy of neighbours and prevent overlooking, in accordance with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 18 - Notwithstanding the provisions of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015, or any future re-enactment of that Order, no satellite dishes, telecommunications masts or equipment or associated structures, shall be installed on the building without the prior written approval of the local planning authority. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2015/7203.
To protect the appearance of the building, and accord with Council policy DMS9

Condition : 19 - No water tanks, plant, lift rooms or other structures (except those shown on the approved planning application drawings) shall be erected upon the roofs of the approved buildings without the written approval of the local planning authority.
To control the appearance of the buildings and safeguard the appearance of the area, in accordance with Council policy DMS1

Condition : 20 - Anti-vibration treatment at the top of the pile caps of the buildings must be implemented on the buildings closest to the railway to reduce the impact of vibration to occupiers of those units, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.
To protect the occupiers of the buildings, in accordance with Council policy DMH4(ii)

Condition : 21 - The cycle storage provision shown on the approved drawings shall be provided before the occupation of each associated phase of the development and shall be retained permanently thereafter for users of the development and for no other purpose. 
To provide cycle parking in accordance with policy DMT2(ii)

Condition : 22 - Details of the sustainability/energy reduction measures and renewable energy measures shall be submitted to and approved in writing before commencement of development (excluding demolition). The approved details shall be implemented in compliance with the details approved by reference 2013/2522, policy DMS3 and thereafter maintained, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority. 
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3

Condition : 23 - The residential units hereby approved shall be built to a minimum standard Code for Sustainable Homes Level 4, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3

Condition : 24 - All residential units should be built to lifetime homes standard.
To provide housing in accordance with Policy IS5.

Condition : 25 - Within 3 months of work starting on site (excluding demolition) in each phase, a Code for Sustainable Homes Interim (Design Stage) Certificate, issued by the Building Research Establishment (BRE) (or equivalent accredited body) must be submitted to the local planning authority to show that a minimum Level 4 rating will be achieved for the dwellings. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2014/1225.
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3

Condition : 26 - Prior to first occupation of each building, a post-completion from an accredited body confirming compliance with policy DMS3 and that the dwellings achieve Level 4 and the Energy Performance Certificate must be submitted to the local planning authority.  Following occupation of the dwellings the developer shall, within 7 days of receipt of the BRE Code for Sustainable Homes Final (Post-Construction) Certificate, issue it to the local planning authority. All the measures integrated shall be retained for as long as the development is in existence, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority. 
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3

Condition : 27 - Within 3 months of work starting on site (excluding demolition) in phases 2 and 3, a BREEAM Interim (Design Stage) Certificate, issued by the Building Research Establishment (BRE) (or equivalent accredited body), must be submitted to the local planning authority to confirm compliance with policy DMS3 and show that an Excellent rating will be achieved for the commercial and community units.
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3

Condition : 28 - The commercial and community units hereby approved should be built to BREEAM (Excellent), unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3

Condition : 29 - Prior to occupation of the approved commercial and community units a copy of the Post Construction Certificate verifying the BREEAM rating of Excellent shall be submitted to the local planning authority to confirm compliance with policy DMS3.  All the measures integrated shall be retained for as long as the development is in existence, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.
To provide sustainable design in accordance with policy DMS3.

Condition : 30 - Schedules of the affordable housing service charge shall be provided annually for the first five years following practical completion of each phase of the development.
To ensure that the units remain affordable in accordance with policy IS5

Condition : 31 - The development shall take place in accordance with approved car parking plan (ref 1615_DWG_PL_xx_016_00) as well as details approved under reference 2013/1950, ensuring that the headroom of the vehicular access into the Phase 1 basement car park is sufficient to cater for wheelchair accessible vehicles (at least 2.60m headroom) and complemented with mounted 'height restriction signage'.  
To ensure adequate access to the parking in accordance with policy DMT2

Condition : 32 - For each phase of development details of the enclosed secure cycle parking spaces (total 774) shall be submitted to the local planning authority for approval. The approved details shall be implemented in accordance with the approved details. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2434.
To provide cycle parking in accordance with policy DMT2(ii)

Condition : 33 - The surface water discharge from the site shall be limited to 18.2l/s, as detailed in paragraph 6.5 of the FRA.
To reduce flood risk in accordance with policy DMS5

Condition : 34 - Development shall not begin (excluding demolition) until a sustainable surface water drainage scheme for the site (including provision of green roofs, sub-surface level tanks, porous paving) as described in paragraphs 6.6, 6.7, 6.8 and Appendix F of the FRA has been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. The drainage strategy should demonstrate the surface water run-off generated up to and including the 100yr critical storm will not exceed the run-off from the undeveloped site following the corresponding rainfall event, and so not increase the risk of flooding both on or off-site. The scheme shall subsequently be implemented in accordance with the approved details before the development is completed. Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2013/2434.
To reduce flood risk in accordance with policy DMS5

Condition : 35 - In all areas of the site where there is overlying made ground present and where gardens or soft landscaping are proposed, then a minimum of 600mm certified clean soil cover shall be provided as a replacement and/or cover of the made ground. Upon completion of all groundworks and landscaping for each phase of development, a verification report shall be submitted for the Council's approval that demonstrates that the requirements of this condition have been achieved.
To comply with policy DMS1 regarding existing contamination.

Condition : 36 - An overarching Arts Strategy for the site, informed through discussions with Wandsworth Arts and Planning Services, shall be submitted to the local planning authority for approval prior to commencement of above ground works (excluding demolition). This should include how art work will be integrated into the buildings and/or landscaping of the development, relating to the site and local area. The details approved in writing shall be implemented in accordance with a programme agreed in writing with the local planning authority.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by references 2014/2848, 2014/6258, and 2015/5619.
In the interests of the visual amenity of the development and quality of the environment in accordance with policy DMS1

Condition : 37 - For each phase of development, works shall take place in accordance with the programme of archaeological recording, photographic recording and survey work of the standing historic building(s), in accordance with the relevant details approved by reference 2012/5826. 
To comply with policy DMS2.

Condition : 38 - For each phase, development (excluding demolition) shall not take place until the applicant has secured the implementation of a programme of archaeological work in accordance with a written scheme for investigation which has been submitted by the applicant and approved by the local planning authority. The development shall only take place in accordance with the detailed scheme pursuant to this condition. The archaeological works shall be carried out by a suitably qualified investigating body acceptable to the local planning authority.  Phase 1 shall be undertaken in accordance with the details approved by reference 2012/5826.
To comply with policy DMS2.

Condition : 39 - Prior to the commencement of phase 3 of the development (excluding demolition), the applicant shall submit a Vacancy Strategy for approval by the local planning authority. The approved strategy shall be implemented in full once the commercial units have been built to shell and core unless otherwise agreed in writing by the local planning authority.  
To preserve the vitality of the town centre in accordance with policy DMTS1

Condition : 40 - Prior to first occupation of each commercial and community building, details and times of servicing and delivery to the building shall be submitted and approved by the local planning authority.  The uses shall operate in accordance with the approved details.
To comply with policy DMS1c
